{"TopicId":130027,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Pale Red *Dots* ESO | Proxima b confirmed UPDATE 2017 PaleRedDots!!","CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T14:43:41Z","PageNum":2,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T18:14:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364885\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452967550\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142607\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022legoclone09\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, legoclone09 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRight, I forgot about the faked moon landing people.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup, And I\u0027m pretty sure that when we go to Mars, they\u0027ll dredge it up before being smacked down by everyone who actually has an education in how radiation works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"legoclone09","CreatedById":142607,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T18:18:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364896\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452968047\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYup, And I\u0027m pretty sure that when we go to Mars, they\u0027ll dredge it up before being smacked down by everyone who actually has an education in how radiation works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but let\u0027s stay on topic. I don\u0027t have much else to say about this right now, so I\u0027m going to go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T18:19:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364902\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452968304\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022142607\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022legoclone09\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, legoclone09 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah, but let\u0027s stay on topic. I don\u0027t have much else to say about this right now, so I\u0027m going to go.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlright.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AngelLestat","CreatedById":58968,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T18:29:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis nice to see astronomers focusing energy in what really matters (at least for us)\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut there is a problem.. they hope to find an earth like planet.. \u00A0but I guess their are talking about \u0022similar size\u0022. \u00A0Because I dont think we have the accuracy yet to discover an earth like planet at venus distance or\u00A0beyond. \u00A0The amount of force that earth does over the sun at this distance is almost zero. \u00A0So I think it can not be found a\u00A0habitable planet with this method. \u00A0Even if there is ten of them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T18:34:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364914\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452968951\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258968\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AngelLestat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, AngelLestat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis nice to see astronomers focusing energy in what really matters (at least for us)\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut there is a problem.. they hope to find an earth like planet.. \u00A0but I guess their are talking about \u0022similar size\u0022. \u00A0Because I dont think we have the accuracy yet to discover an earth like planet at venus distance or\u00A0beyond. \u00A0The amount of force that earth does over the sun at this distance is almost zero. \u00A0So I think it can not be found a\u00A0habitable planet with this method. \u00A0Even if there is ten of them.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf it orbits the nearest star (Other than the Sun) which is a very small red dwarf, (I.e. If a planet is in the Habitable zone, it\u0027d have an orbital period of 6-27 days.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m pretty sure we can find something similar to Earth. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-17T01:40:11Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2016 01:40  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AngelLestat","CreatedById":58968,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T18:46:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nahh, I thought they were talking about alpha centauri A and B (focusing in B), when they show in the video the 2 stars.. I was expecting the short scale between A and B XD\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn that case yeah.. is possible. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will be existing\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T18:50:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364933\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452969963\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002258968\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AngelLestat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, AngelLestat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nahh, I thought they were talking about alpha centauri A and B (focusing in B), when they show in the video the 2 stars.. I was expecting the short scale between A and B XD\u003Cbr\u003E\nIn that case yeah.. is possible. \u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt will be existing\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhhh, whatever. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E Anyway, what do you think the best result could be? Smaller than Earth? Same size as Earth? Larger than Earth? Warmer, cooler? what would you like to see?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T18:58:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is exciting, but I\u0027m much more eager for them to send something to land (or swim) on Encelidus!\u003Cbr\u003E\nLittle off-topic, but IMO, that\u0027s the real hot-spot to explore right now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-16T18:59:25Z\u0022 title=\u002201/16/2016 06:59  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Just Jim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T19:03:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364952\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452970721\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is exciting, but I\u0027m much more eager for them to send something to land (or swim) on Encelidus!\u003Cbr\u003E\nLittle off-topic, but IMO, that\u0027s the real hot-spot to explore right now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*Enceladus But that would be cool. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBack on topic, about the comment above yours, what would you like to see with a possible habitable exoplanet around Proxima?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Motokid600","CreatedById":66349,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T19:07:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to see Methane. Oxygen, Nitrogen. Water. City lights.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou know... Simple stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T19:08:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs some of us know, red dwarfs are problematic because planets around them may be \u0022Tidally locked\u0022, hence, may not be habitable. So here\u0027s some research on the issue. Tidally locked exoplanets may be more habitable than we thought: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.gizmag.com/tidally-locked-exoplanets-potentially-habitable/39407/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.gizmag.com/tidally-locked-exoplanets-potentially-habitable/39407/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn Atmosphere may be key for planets around red dwarfs\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.space.com/28280-alien-planets-atmospheres-day-night.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E http://www.space.com/28280-alien-planets-atmospheres-day-night.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364970\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452971223\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Motokid600\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Motokid600 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to see Methane. Oxygen, Nitrogen. Water. City lights.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou know... Simple stuff.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about the size/orbital period? What you like to see?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-16T19:09:06Z\u0022 title=\u002201/16/2016 07:09  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fredinno","CreatedById":143381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T19:48:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364972\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452971321\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n39 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn Atmosphere may be key for planets around red dwarfs\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.space.com/28280-alien-planets-atmospheres-day-night.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E http://www.space.com/28280-alien-planets-atmospheres-day-night.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo S**t. Isn\u0027t that obvious?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T19:55:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365031\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452973727\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022fredinno\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, fredinno said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo S**t. Isn\u0027t that obvious?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYeah.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E But I meant, \u0022A thin atmosphere like Earths may be the key of giving planets around red dwarfs day/night cycles\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Motokid600","CreatedById":66349,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T23:16:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364972\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452971321\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat about the size/orbital period? What you like to see?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRealistically? Because I\u0027d like to see another Earth, but that\u0027s not going to happen. When it comes to planet formation I like to think of it like this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPicture a vat the size of a building filled with millions upon millions of those six sides dice. Tip the vat over and after it all settles tally up the numbers. You get Earth. Change one number and you get Venus.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo predicting what we\u0027ll see is impossible. So realistically what I\u0027d like to see is... Maybe a water world. Twice the size of Earth, no land mass and a thick atmosphere with a high ratio of oxygen.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose environmental combinations could lead to the largest, most alien sea creatures imaginable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T23:20:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365362\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452986215\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002266349\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Motokid600\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Motokid600 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRealistically? Because I\u0027d like to see another Earth, but that\u0027s not going to happen. When it comes to planet formation I like to think of it like this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPicture a vat the size of a building filled with millions upon millions of those six sides dice. Tip the vat over and after it all settles tally up the numbers. You get Earth. Change one number and you get Venus.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo predicting what we\u0027ll see is impossible. So realistically what I\u0027d like to see is... Maybe a water world. Twice the size of Earth, no land mass and a thick atmosphere with a high ratio of oxygen.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose environmental combinations could lead to the largest, most alien sea creatures imaginable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to see a planet 1.5x the mass of the Earth, and 1.2x the radii of Earth covered in 80% water, with a pressure of 1.1 atmospheres with 19% O2, and a day/night cycle of 32 hours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-16T23:21:13Z\u0022 title=\u002201/16/2016 11:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T23:48:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365368\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452986454\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d like to see a planet 1.5x the mass of the Earth, and 1.2x the radii of Earth covered in 80% water, with a pressure of 1.1 atmospheres with 19% O2, and a day/night cycle of 32 hours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy does this sound so familiar?\u003Cbr\u003E\nIs it Arrakis by chance?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T23:52:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365413\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452988087\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy does this sound so familiar?\u003Cbr\u003E\nIs it Arrakis by chance?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo.... I\u0027ve never heard of that series, plus, it isn\u0027t a desert world.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T23:57:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365424\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452988330\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo.... I\u0027ve never heard of that series, plus, it isn\u0027t a desert world.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh wait....... I actually said the wrong planet... but correct series.\u00A0I meant Caladan. That was a major goof.\u00A0 Opps....\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut seriously, is that something you came up with?\u00A0 Or are you thinking of a particular planet?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-16T23:59:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365433\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452988648\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh wait....... I actually said the wrong planet... but correct series.\u00A0I meant Caladan. That was a major goof.\u00A0 Opps....\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:confused:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_huh.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:confused:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut seriously, is that something you came up with?\u00A0 Or are you thinking of a particular planet?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool... but no, I was just thinking of a planet that I thought up for a possible book I\u0027m considering writing, around Lalande 21185.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T00:01:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365441\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452988794\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCool... but no, I was just thinking of a planet that I thought up for a possible book I\u0027m considering writing, around Lalande 21185.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhhh, gotcha\u00A0\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBack on topic, given how much stuff they seem to be finding around other stars, I have to think there\u0027s something around Proxima.\u00A0 Planet or big bunch of asteroids... that\u0027s hard to say for now.\u00A0 But based on how many other exo-planets and such they\u0027re finding, it seems the odds of it having\u00A0at least a dwarf-planet\u00A0are increasing all the time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-17T00:06:22Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2016 12:06  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Just Jim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T00:02:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365444\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452988891\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhhh, gotcha\u00A0\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what kind of planet would you like to see around Proxima, assuming there\u0027s a habitable exoplanet around it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fredinno","CreatedById":143381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T00:06:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364872\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452966563\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPart of the reason, I believe, is that the public didn\u0027t want anything related to nuclear in LEO, they thought that if something went wrong, the radiation would be spread across the world and everyone would die:/\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLuckily, the dream hasn\u0027t died: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://news.discovery.com/space/galaxies/want-a-starship-think-big-think-really-big-131029.htm\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://news.discovery.com/space/galaxies/want-a-starship-think-big-think-really-big-131029.htm\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEspecially since the first plans involved blowing nukes up in the atmosphere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365448\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452988971\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what kind of planet would you like to see around Proxima, assuming there\u0027s a habitable exoplanet around it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-17T00:20:40Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2016 12:20  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by fredinno\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Just Jim","CreatedById":148725,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T00:17:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365448\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452988971\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo what kind of planet would you like to see around Proxima, assuming there\u0027s a habitable exoplanet around it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nme?\u00A0 This is just a guess... but Proxima is small and cool, as far as stars go, so if there\u0027s anything habitable, I think would be a small\u00A0ice planet, similar to Enceladus or Europa.\u00A0 I know those are moons, but I think something similar might happen, if there\u0027s available water or ice in the surrounding space when it formed.\u00A0 And if the gravitational pull of A and/or B Centauri is high enough to\u00A0get some geo-thermal activity to keep the core warm enough, you may get the same kind of ocean under the ice like they\u0027re finding on Enceladus.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-17T00:19:43Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2016 12:19  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Just Jim\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Eforgot a word\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"fredinno","CreatedById":143381,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T00:18:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222364972\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452971321\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152800\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spaceception\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Spaceception said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs some of us know, red dwarfs are problematic because planets around them may be \u0022Tidally locked\u0022, hence, may not be habitable\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProxima is also a flare star, making life more difficult due to radiation bursts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spaceception","CreatedById":152800,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-01-17T00:29:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365444\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452988891\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022148725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Just Jim\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n34 minutes ago, Just Jim said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAhhh, gotcha\u00A0\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:wink:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_wink.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:wink:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBack on topic, given how much stuff they seem to be finding around other stars, I have to think there\u0027s something around Proxima.\u00A0 Planet or big bunch of asteroids... that\u0027s hard to say for now.\u00A0 But based on how many other exo-planets and such they\u0027re finding, it seems the odds of it having\u00A0at least a dwarf-planet\u00A0are increasing all the time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nExactly \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPlus, studies have been done that estimate that red dwarfs have at least one planet, and at least a quarter of them have planets in the habitable zone, so they worked out that the nearest \u0022Earth-twin\u0022 should be 6-8 ly away (I can\u0027t find the picture\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:mad:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022true\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_angry.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:mad:\u0022\u003E), but depending on certain conditions, could be closer.. Like around Proxima!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222365474\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022130027\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221452989902\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022143381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022fredinno\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n17 minutes ago, fredinno said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProxima is also a flare star, making life more difficult due to radiation bursts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the planet has a strong enough magnetic field, and is lucky enough, It could be fine.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, here\u0027s a simple, but cool calculator: \u003Ca href=\u0022http://astro.unl.edu/naap/habitablezones/animations/stellarHabitableZone.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://astro.unl.edu/naap/habitablezones/animations/stellarHabitableZone.html\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-01-17T00:36:00Z\u0022 title=\u002201/17/2016 12:36  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00228 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 17, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Spaceception\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}